{"id":"tv-df7","title":"Centralize optional FFI access pattern in environment.py","description":"
environment.py has 36 instances of this defensive pattern:

```python
fn = getattr(self.lib, "tribal_village_some_function", None)
if fn is None:
    return <default>
fn.argtypes = [...]
fn.restype = ...
return fn(...)
```

Create a helper method on the class:

```python
def _optional_ffi(self, name: str, argtypes: list, restype, *args, default=None):
    fn = getattr(self.lib, name, None)
    if fn is None:
        return default
    fn.argtypes = argtypes
    fn.restype = restype
    return fn(*args)
```

Then replace all 36 instances with calls to `self._optional_ffi(...)`.

This is a pure refactor — behavior should be identical. Run `uv run tribal-village play -r ansi -s 3` to verify.
